{
  "texts": [
    "Among the 301 images, 187 are normal and 114 are abnormal.",
    "Image PreprocessingThe retinal images are preprocessed by resizing images and selecting the proper filter from the RGB image.",
    "Typically, MSE (Mean Squared Error), PSNR (Peak Signal-to-Noise Ratio), and SNR (Signal-to-Noise Ratio) are metrics used to evaluate the quality and performance of image processing algorithms, including filtering techniques.",
    "They provide quantitative measures of the distortion, noise level, and signal fidelity in processed images.",
    "Based on this PSNR, SNR, and MSE values the filter are selected."
  ]
}